# Microsoft Sentinel Threat Detection Lab Setup

## Project Overview

This lab demonstrates the deployment of a cloud-based Security Operations Center (SOC) using Microsoft Sentinel and Microsoft Azure services. The objective was to simulate real-world security monitoring by collecting Windows Security Events, writing Kusto Query Language (KQL) queries, creating Microsoft Sentinel analytics rules, and investigating security incidents.

---

# Lab Objectives

- Deploy Microsoft Sentinel.
- Connect a Windows endpoint using Azure Arc.
- Install Azure Monitor Agent (AMA).
- Configure Data Collection Rules (DCR).
- Collect Windows Security Events.
- Create KQL detection queries.
- Develop Microsoft Sentinel Analytics Rules.
- Perform Threat Hunting.
- Generate and investigate security incidents.
- Document findings using MITRE ATT&CK.

